  "doc_id": "25905",
  "text": "ER-α and PR are classic nuclear transcription factors [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] . HER2 is a member of the EGF receptor tyrosine kinase family and has been rigorously studied as a signaling molecule of the cell membrane [CITATION_3] . However, recent studies have reported that HER2 is also expressed in the nucleus and could form a complex at a specific nucleotide sequence of the gene promoter to stimulate its transcription [CITATION_4] [CITATION_5] . ER-α, PR and HER2 play key roles in breast cancer; however, whether loss of the three factors contributes to deregulate genes that participate in the progress of TNBC remains unknown.",
